msContents.summary: Lacunose copy of an illustrated Persian translation of a book of astronomy, mostly focused on the constellations; constellation illustrations from two sides have been transferred by pounce and are sometimes not completely inked or painted (see f. 52v, for example). Others have been outlined by pricking (see f. 58 lower illustrations, for example).

supportDesc.extent: vi + 130 + vii foliated leaves : 237 x 167 (180 x 110) mm, bound to 237 x 167 mm

layoutDesc.layout: 23 lines per page and occasional tables of variable dimensions.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in nastaʻlīq in black ink; pointed.

decoDesc.decoNote: 65 illustrations of constellations, often in color; numerous tables in red and black; rubrications in red.

origin.p: The item is undated; probably copied in the 18th or 19th century.
